<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="3" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1985,2010]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="3" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1985,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The male of this species shows some similarities to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wells 1993" authorityName="Wells" authorityYear="1993" box="[866,1194,1985,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Microptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pasak">
<emphasis box="[866,1057,1985,2009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="107">Microptila pasak</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wells" box="[1065,1194,1985,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="107" refString="Wells, A. (1993) Micro-caddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) from Bali, Indonesia. Zoologische Mededekingen Leiden, 67, 351 - 359." type="journal article" year="1993">Wells 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingRegion box="[1382,1431,1985,2010]" country="Indonesia" name="Bali" pageId="3" pageNumber="107">Bali</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,263,151,176]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, in having the subgenital plate bilobed distally, these lobes divergent, and a short apical or subapical process on each inferior appendage, but is distinguished from that species as follows: (1) Segment IX with rounded posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[399,465,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A, 
<emphasis box="[501,521,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">cf</emphasis>
, IX with digitiform lobes laterally in 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1052,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Microptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pasak">
<emphasis box="[949,1052,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">M. pasak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) the caudal excavation of the subgenital plate is narrow and deep (
<figureCitation box="[575,644,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B, 3D, 
<emphasis box="[729,749,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">cf</emphasis>
, the excavation wide and shallow in 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1284,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Microptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pasak">
<emphasis box="[1179,1284,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">M. pasak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and (3) the inferior appendages each have a short mesal process subapically (
<figureCitation box="[889,966,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
A,3C,3E, 
<emphasis box="[1079,1099,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">cf</emphasis>
. the inferior appendages each have a peg-like process at the mesal-caudal corner in 
<taxonomicName box="[750,853,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Microptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pasak">
<emphasis box="[750,853,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="108">M. pasak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
