<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="5" pageNumber="109" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1617,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1617,1642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Male</emphasis>
. Length of each forewing and hind wing 
<quantity box="[723,858,1617,1642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.6 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[911,999,1617,1641]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, respectively (n = 2). Antennae 18–19- segmented and 
<quantity box="[325,411,1653,1678]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long (n = 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1617,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[317,392,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
A–3F). Segment IX (IX) annular, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[945,1010,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B) excavation of anterior margin deep and semi-circular, excavation of posterior margin deep and quadrate, transverse tegmental bridge broad, dorsal midline about 1/5 as long as segment IX; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[796,861,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C) excavation of anterior margin shallow and semicircular, excavation of posterior margin shallow and quadrate. Tergite X (t X) quadrate, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1407,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B) with subquadrate excavation caudally, semimembranous and transparent with lateral margins lightly sclerotized. Subgenital plate (sg plate) large, strongly sclerotized, margins of basal half rounded laterally, distally bilobed, lobes slightly divergent (
<figureCitation box="[371,452,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
B, 3D); in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[740,809,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A) stout, rod-shaped, slightly curved ventrad. Inferior appendages (inf app) large, setose; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[729,795,1941,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A) main article stout at basal 4/5 and strongly tapered in apical 1/5; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[466,532,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C) apices incurved, in ventral and ventromesal views (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1222,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C, 3E) blunt mesal process subapically. Phallus long, slender, titillator (ti) arising at apical 1/3, encircling phallus 1.5 times (
<figureCitation box="[1326,1392,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1485]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,197,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[261,1324,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microptila nakama sp. nov. male, type specimens. 3 A, genitalia, left lateral; 3 B, same, dorsal; 3 C, same, ventral; 3 D, subgenital plate, dorsal; 3 E, left inferior appendage, ventromesal; 3 F, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: IX – X = abdominal segments IX – X; inf app = inferior appendage (paired); ph = phallus; sg plate = subgenital plate; ti = titillator; t X = tergite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
